sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Polyargini
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Trojan peptides are short sequences that penetrate through the plasma membrane inside the cell without the need of any receptor or endocitosis process [Derossi 1998]. They can be used to increase the efficiency with which a protein enters a cell.
This part is Polyarginine, and has to be used just before the coding sequence of the peptide that you want to be import enhanced.
(refer to ''Characterisation of cell-penetrating peptide-mediated peptide delivery'' [Jones et al 2005] for more information about polyarginine)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Characterisation of cell-penetrating peptide-mediated peptide delivery [Jones et al 2005]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Sequence obtained by retro-translation. Codon and mRNA-secondary structure optimized for yeast.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K416003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This secretion tag when linked to the N-terminal of the protein directs extracellular secretion of the protein. After targeting through the ER to the golgi, this "pre-pro" tag is cleaved by the KEX-2 protease resulting in secretion of protein without the aforementioned tag. To use this tag, attached it directly upstream of your proteins CDS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Phair
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was sent to use from Dr. Sheldon Park of the University of Buffalo.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There was an illegal Xbal1 site at bp 101 and we removed it through altering the primers necessary for biobricking the sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PolyHb
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Stable and soluble Histidine rich peptide.
This part has a '''HindIII''' restriction site as extra.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
PolyHb was desing taking into acount the following consideration: # avoided repeating the same residue in tandem to minimize local tRNA depleation # avoided Trp in tandem because of therir low solubility # we included Gly to avoid the formation of stable structures # included acidic and basic amino acids to increase solubility
Sequence obtained by retro-translation. Codon and mRNA-secondary structure optimized for yeast.
